Polyline does not respond to setBounds().  The reason is because it calculates 
its own bounds as a function of its PointList.

Supporting both setBounds() and setPoints() would be troublesome because 
setting the Points after you have positioned the Polyline would move it to 
wherever the new points are.  It would be a last-one-in-wins scenario.

We could investigate making this work, but getPreferredSize() could not be 
implemented without laying-out the connection, which is the reverse of the 
typical validate order.  You would have to layout the connection to know how 
the decorations affect the total size.
Maybe I misunderstand something, but is there a workaround possible today?

I want do create customized figures with Polylines. Currently points of 
Polylines must be absolute coordinates? So it won't be possible to use these 
figures for EditParts?

What do you suggest? Do I have to create my own figure implementation extending 
Shape?

I don't want to use fixed images for the EditPart figures because I want to use 
zoom functionality later.
More info on the newsgroup.
This is the same issue as 27227. I should have marked that one as the 
duplicate, but it's already closed.

